HOUSE RESOLUTION 180
By Hill
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Mary Ann Blessing of
Bristol.
WHEREAS, the members of this legislative body were greatly saddened to learn of the
passing of Mary Ann Blessing of Bristol; and
WHEREAS, born in Rockville, Maryland, Mary Ann Blessing lived a life marked by
unwavering faith, quiet strength, and tireless service to others; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Blessing built a life centered on faith and family with her husband of
forty-three years, Herschel Blessing; and
WHEREAS, for more than forty years, Mary Ann Blessing devoted her life to serving
others through ministry and her work with Kingsway Charities, which has made an outstanding
global impact; and
WHEREAS, since 2000, Kingsway Charities has distributed over $4.1 billion in
medications and medical supplies worldwide; in 2025 alone, the ministry distributed over $483
million in medications and medical supplies, completed 374 relief trips, shipped twenty-four
international containers, and inspired 2,834 volunteer hours; and
WHEREAS, while working with the ministry, Mrs. Blessing's greatest joy was seeing the
22,710 individuals accept Christ; she was on fire for God, a prayer warrior, and a behind-the-
scenes leader who faithfully answered God's call; and
WHEREAS, Mary Ann Blessing will be remembered for her deep faith in Jesus Christ
and love of her family and friends; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Blessing is survived by her children, Greg (Shana), Ben (Lydia), and
MaryBeth (Lucas); her grandchildren, Alex, Avery, Anderson, Aniston, Aiden, Annabelle,
HR0180
016440
- 1 -

Addilyn, and Eleanor; her brothers, Henry, Jim (April), John (Joan), Joe (Cindy), and Jeff (Terri);
and a host of friends; and
WHEREAS, she was preceded in death by her parents, Lloyd and Mary Gregory, and a
sister-in-law, Jeanie; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should pay tribute to her bountiful life of purpose and
service; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we honor the
memory of Mary Ann Blessing, reflecting fondly upon her impeccable character and her stalwart
commitment to living the examined life with courage and conviction. We express our sympathy
and offer our condolences to the family and friends of Mrs. Blessing.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
